  "instructions": [
    "preheat oven to 400f.",
    "season chicken thighs with caraway seeds, salt, and pepper.",
    "caramelize onions in vegetable oil by cooking slowly over medium heat for 20 minutes.",
    "in a large bowl, whisk together chicken stock concentrate, apple cider vinegar, and water to make the goulash stock.",
    "add the cooked onions, garlic, and flour to the bowl and whisk until smooth.",
    "heat the mixture over medium heat, stirring continuously, until it thickens.",
    "add the chicken thighs to the bowl and coat with the goulash stock mixture.",
    "transfer the mixture to a baking dish and bake for 25 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through.",
    "serve hot, garnished with chopped parsley and crushed saltines, and topped with a dollop of sour cream if desired.",
    "cover and refrigerate leftover goulash for up to 3 days."
  ],
